body: 63 (return) [ The Greeks, who disliked the union, were unwilling to sally from this strong fortress, (p. 178, 193, 195, 202, of Syropulus.) The shame of the Latins was aggravated by their producing an old MS. of the second council of Nice, with _filioque_ in the Nicene creed. A palpable forgery! (p. 173.)]
